# Directly set the pose and velocity of one or more MuJoCo free-joint objects, each
# identified by the name of the body it drives. Intended for teleporting/resetting objects in
# the world (e.g. a manipulable prop), similar to Gazebo's set_entity_state.
#
# Application is atomic across the whole list: every entry is validated (body exists, is
# driven by a free joint, and any pose/twist frame_id names a known body) before anything is
# written. If any entry is invalid, the entire request is rejected and no sim data is
# modified. If the same body name appears more than once, entries are applied in order, so
# the last one wins.

# List of free-joint bodies to set, see FreeJointState.msg for per-entry fields.
FreeJointState[] free_joints

---

# True if every entry's body was found, driven by a free joint, and the state was applied.
bool success

# Human-readable status / error description (e.g. unknown body, not a free joint).
# On failure, identifies which entry (index and body name) caused the rejection.
string message
